info.name: Merchant API v1.0 (id_02@demo.id)
info.description:
This set of API is for merchant or biller to request for **QR payment and** **Send money .**

# Authentication

- Please login to merchant portal and you will see **OAuth** menu.
- In the menu you will find **Client ID** and **Client Secret** and button to generate **Access token** and **Refresh token**.
- **Access token** is used in token-based authentication to allow an application to access an API.
- **Refresh token** is used refresh token API to generate new Access token when the Access token expired.
    

# Callback

- Callback to merchant is API request initiaited from our system back to merchant system
- **Request QR** and **Send Money** API is asynchronous communication
- Inform your endpoint for notify result of payment or sendmoney.
    

# Callback Type

- QR Payment
- Send Money
    

# Callback Status Code

- **QR Payment**
    - **11** QR payment successfully
    - **12** QR Payment reject
- **Send Money**
    - **31** Sendmoney successfully
    - **32** Sendmoney rejected.

# Response Status

- Use **HTTP response status statndard codes** to indicate request has been success.
- See detail [HTTP response status codes](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Status)
- Status code 200 is success.
- Other status accept 200 is fail. and you will see message and error in body.
